> Mustard is one of our favorite secret weapons in the kitchen; it instantly adds a mellow, tangy punch to anything it touches. It's perfectly folded into this warm potato salad. Quick-cooking chicken paillard helps put this dinner on the table in no time at all!

Cook the potatoes: Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into 3⁄4-inch cubes. Place
the potatoes in a medium #pot{} with a large pinch of @salt{} and enough water to
cover. Bring the water to a boil and cook the potatoes for about ~{15%minutes},
until fork tender. Remove with a #slotted spoon{}, keeping the water boiling
on the stove.

Prep the ingredients: Meanwhile, halve, peel and mince 1⁄4 cup @Red Onion{1}(halved,
peeled and minced). Finely dice the @Celery{1%unit}(finely diced). Finely chop the
@Parsley{¼%ounce}(finely chopped). Halve the @Green Beans{6%ounce}(halved lengthwise).

Butterfly the chicken breasts: With your hand on top of the @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce},
slice carefully into the center of the meat, parallel to your #cutting board{},
until the chicken is sliced almost through. Open the chicken like a book and
season all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Repeat with the other chicken breast.
Place the chicken between two pieces of #plastic wrap{} and pound with a #mallet{}
or heavy pan until the chicken is 1⁄2-inch thick.

Cook the chicken: Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{7%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Working in batches, if necessary, add the chicken to the pan
and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until fully cooked through. Set aside to
rest for ~{5%minutes}, then thinly slice against the grain.

Cook the beans: Add the green beans to the same pot used for the potatoes and
cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, until just tender. Drain the beans and rinse under
cold water.

== Potato Salad ==

Make the potato salad: In a large #bowl{}, mix together the @Sour Cream{1%ounce},
1 teaspoon @Whole Grain Mustard{1%tablespoon}, 1⁄2 Tablespoon
@Red Wine Vinegar{2%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Carefully toss
in the potatoes, celery, chopped parsley, green beans, and minced onion (to
taste).

== To Serve ==

Plate: Serve the sliced chicken on a bed of mustard potato and green bean salad
and enjoy!